    # game/traveling.rpy:752
    old "Some parts of the road lead uphill, some downhill. The forests are lush, but not too dark. The few foraging deer and boars keep their distance, and the birds are disinterested in your presence, singing cheerfully and preening their feathers. Sounds of an ongoing hunt reach you from the east, but none of the nearby creatures seem bothered. \n\nOnce you get farther north, the colorful meadow reveals tall hills on the other side of the stream, but the road leads through a valley. There’s a gentle plume of smoke coming from one of the mountains in the west. "
    new ""

