    # game/traveling.rpy:766
    old "The forests are lush, but not too dark, and for most of the time you’re surrounded by yellow meadows. The few foraging deer and boars keep their distance, and the birds are disinterested in your presence, singing cheerfully and preening their feathers. Sounds of an ongoing hunt reach you from the east, but none of the nearby creatures seem bothered. \n\nYou see the tall hills in the south, but the road leads through a valley. There’s a gentle plume of smoke coming from one of the mountains in the west. "
    new ""

    # game/traveling.rpy:783
    old "For most of the time you’re surrounded by yellow meadows. The trees on your left get sparser, while the few lonely birches on your right still bear the signs of tapping - marked with knife cuts, tied with cords. Some of them still carry wooden vessels, as if they were simply abandoned, maybe last spring, maybe before that. A few of the trees are already dried-out, and the winds managed to knock them down. \n\nAs you get closer to the crossroads, the ground gets muddy. The beaten path avoids the wetlands as much as it can. The screeches and hisses mix with the buzzing of insects, and as you reach a small pond, there are signs of blood on its bank. The air is moist and heavy, and has a hint of rotting meat to it. "
    new ""

    # game/traveling.rpy:783
    old "Better to avoid the bogs when night time approaches. Such places rarely have fine roads."
    new ""

    # game/traveling.rpy:783
    old "It may still be early, but it’s better to avoid the bogs when night time approaches. Such places rarely have fine roads."
