    # game/traveling.rpy:799
    old "The trees on your right get sparser, replaced by yellow meadows and marshes. There are a few lonely birches around, still bearing the signs of tapping - marked with knife cuts, tied with cords. Some of them still carry wooden vessels, as if they were simply abandoned, maybe last spring, maybe before that. A few of the trees are already dried-out, and the winds managed to knock them down. \n\nAs you get closer to the crossroads, the ground gets muddy. The beaten path avoids the wetlands as much as it can. The screeches and hisses mix with the buzzing of insects, and as you reach a small pond, there are signs of blood on its bank. The air is moist and heavy, and has a hint of rotting meat to it. "
