    # game/traveling.rpy:867
    old "The road twists between the flooded purplish grasses. The field ahead of you is still green, bearing the second sowing of broad beans, maybe the third one, if the land allows it. \n\nThe {i}workers{/i} ignore you. Some of them are nothing but bones, some carry scraps of flesh, wearing them like forgotten rags, and others look almost human, as if they were awoken right after death. Most of the witless shells move around piles of soil, carry wooden logs, or dig in the ground with their bare hands, but there are also those with considerable abilities - they use pitchforks, hoes, and splitting axes, and confidently cross the uneven ground. \n\nThere’s only a few breathing souls in sight. They observe your passing, but keep their distance. "
    new ""

    # game/traveling.rpy:867
    old "As I ride among the undead, I hold my hourglass, praying for protection in this dreary place."
    new ""

    # game/traveling.rpy:867
    old "I keep the blade at hand, just in case."
    new ""

    # game/traveling.rpy:867
    old "They aren’t attacking me, so I don’t need to be afraid. The people who live here seem to have everything under control."
    new ""

    # game/traveling.rpy:888
    old "You follow the road spread between the hills and lonely trees, until you reach a solid, wooden bridge, not older than a generation. You ride uphill, but {color=#f6d6bd}[horsename]{/color} manages to keep up. The dark woods in the south are behind a gently humming creek, while the forest on your right was trimmed by the locals. It’s a peaceful journey, at least for some time. After a few minutes, you spot a group of wolves feasting on a fallen, furry beast, maybe a wisent. One of them looks toward you. "
    new ""

    # game/traveling.rpy:888
    old "I ride a bit faster."
    new ""

    # game/traveling.rpy:888
    old "We ride a bit faster."
    new ""

    # game/traveling.rpy:911
    old "The detour is not as smooth as the main road. A wagon could make it through, but even so, you have to squeeze between some narrow corridors, hoping no beast is going to jump at you from a ledge. You walk, leading your mount, with an axe in your hand. \n\nIn the middle of the road, after reaching one of the higher hills, you take a glance ahead. Even from here you see the sun reflecting from the ocean, but there’s also a pillar of smoke coming from the distant west. There may be a volcano somewhere behind the horizon, but you can’t tell if it’s a part of the peninsula, or maybe a yet stranger land. \n\nOnce you get to the other side of the mountain, you find the northern entrance to the tunnel, blocked by a large, bronze gate, so tall and wide you’re not sure if it’s something you could open with your muscles alone. There’s a key hole as well, as large as your hand. "
    new ""

    # game/traveling.rpy:911
    old "Unlocking the tunnel would save me a lot of time."
    new ""

    # game/traveling.rpy:911
    old "I’m surprised no soul tried to steal the door yet. Or maybe someone tried, but failed."
    new ""

