    new ""

    # game/traveling.rpy:950
    old "{color=#f6d6bd}[horsename]{/color} welcomes the light on the other side of the tunnel. The road now leads downhill, through the meadows, and toward the village placed alongside the stream - even from here, you see the smoke, the tall fortress, and the wide walls. \n\nYou take a look at the crossroad to your left, which is the other end of the detour that leads around the mountain, and partially through it. Exploring the tunnels took a lot of effort, but in the long run, it may save you and other travelers a lot of time. "
    new ""

    # game/traveling.rpy:950
    old "The locals may be glad to learn that the tunnel is clear again."
    new ""

    # game/traveling.rpy:960
    old "The grand, brown-and-gray mountains are blocking the horizon, and you doubt the path is going to reach the snow-covered peaks. Without trees and clouds blocking your view, you’re like an ant approaching a fortress. "
    new ""

    # game/traveling.rpy:960
    old "Let’s hope there are some benches for me to take a break from climbing."
    new ""

    # game/traveling.rpy:960
    old "I wonder what kind of beasts hide among the rocks."
    new ""

    # game/traveling.rpy:975
    old "Seeing how steep this part of the road gets, you dismount. It will be safer for you to get a bit tired now than to push {color=#f6d6bd}[horsename]{/color} onto the verge of fatigue. You take a sip of water and start climbing. \n\nThe road is winding and narrow, but it would fit a single wagon if it wasn’t for the sporadic rocks and boulders blocking the path. Some of the larger ones are resting just in the middle, and as you look above, you struggle to recognize where they came from. "
    new ""

    # game/traveling.rpy:975
    old "They were placed here on purpose."
